Even or Odd Checker:


Task: Create a program that checks if a number is even or odd.
Activity: Let the user change the number and see the result.
Starter Code:
let number = 7; // Change this value
if (number % 2 === 0) {
  console.log(number + " is even.");
} else {
  console.log(number + " is odd.");
}
Temperature Advisor:


Task: Write a program that suggests what to wear based on the temperature.
Activity: Set different temperature values and see if your advice changes.
Starter Code:
let temperature = 72; // Try changing this number
if (temperature < 60) {
  console.log("It's chilly—wear a jacket!");
} else if (temperature <= 80) {
  console.log("Perfect weather for a t-shirt!");
} else {
  console.log("It's hot—stay cool in shorts!");
}
Letter Grader:


Task: Create a program that converts a numerical score to a letter grade.
Activity: Input different scores and test your grade boundaries.
Starter Code:
let score = 85; // Change this value
if (score >= 90) {
  console.log("Grade: A");
} else if (score >= 80) {
  console.log("Grade: B");
} else if (score >= 70) {
  console.log("Grade: C");
} else if (score >= 60) {
  console.log("Grade: D");
} else {
  console.log("Grade: F");
}
Adventure Decision:


Task: Write a program that suggests an adventure based on age.
Activity: Input ages and see which adventure is recommended.
Starter Code:
let age = 16; // Modify the age to test
if (age < 10) {
  console.log("Time for a fun playground visit!");
} else if (age < 18) {
  console.log("How about a thrilling roller coaster ride?");
} else {
  console.log("Adventure awaits with extreme sports!");
}
Guess My Number Game Starter:


Task: Start building your number guessing game by setting a secret number and comparing it with a guess.
Activity: Experiment with different guesses and add hints.
Starter Code:
let secretNumber = 5;
let guess = 3; // Change this to test different outcomes
if (guess === secretNumber) {
  console.log("You guessed it! Great job!");
} else if (guess < secretNumber) {
  console.log("Too low, try guessing higher!");
} else {
  console.log("Too high, try guessing lower!");
}
